@port = 7019
### NOTE: Replace <PORT> with the Identity API's HTTPS port

### Test 1: Basic Role Flattening
### Expected: "Organization Manager" should unwrap into Dashboard, Roster Manage, Scrim Schedule, AND the Parent "Roster.ManageTransfer" should recursively unwrap into TransferRequest and TransferAccept.
POST https://localhost:{{port}}/api/diagnostics/flatten
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "roles": ["Organization Manager"],
    "customPermissions": []
}

###

### Test 2: Custom Permission Injection + Deduplication
### Expected: The user gets "Player" base permissions. We also manually inject "Roster.ManageTransfer". The engine should merge them, recursively unpack the transfer rights, and deduplicate everything perfectly.
POST https://localhost:{{port}}/api/diagnostics/flatten
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "roles": ["Player"],
    "customPermissions": [
        "Roster.ManageTransfer",
        "Analytics.ViewBasic" 
    ]
}

###

### Test 3: Unrecognized Role Resilience
### Expected: The engine ignores "Ghost Role" without crashing, but still successfully flattens "System Administrator".
POST https://localhost:{{port}}/api/diagnostics/flatten
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "roles": ["System Administrator", "Ghost Role"],
    "customPermissions": []
}